TY  - JOUR
AU  - Maxted, Peter
T1  - Present Bias Unconstrained: Consumption, Welfare, and the Present-Bias Dilemma*
PY  - 2025
Y1  - 2025/11/01
DO  - 10.1093/qje/qjaf030
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 140
IS  - 4
SP  - 2963
EP  - 3013
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - By augmenting the continuous-time specification of Harris and Laibson (2013) with the assumption that hard borrowing constraints do not bind in equilibrium, present bias can be tractably incorporated into rich consumption-saving models featuring stochastic income, risky and illiquid assets, and costly borrowing. I present closed-form expressions characterizing how present bias affects consumption, illiquid asset demand, and welfare. This welfare analysis specifies the channels through which present bias can matter for policy and uncovers the present-bias dilemma: present bias can have large welfare costs, but individuals have little ability to alleviate these costs using financial commitment devices like illiquid assets.
Y2  - 4/24/2026
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/qje/qjaf030
ER  - 



